16:58.566 --> 17:02.196
-Oh. that poor man.
-No. no. Bull's okay. He's right here.

17:02.370 --> 17:04.530
His cape fell. You fainted.

17:05.606 --> 17:08.766
-Just like a woman. right?
HARRY: No.

17:08.942 --> 17:11.502
Just like a scared human being.

17:11.678 --> 17:15.508
Mac. why don't you take her to the nurse's
office. and get her checked over. huh?

17:15.681 --> 17:19.851
Yeah. Come on.
Then we'll get a cup of coffee.

17:20.019 --> 17:21.919
BULL:
Wait a minute.

17:26.526 --> 17:28.956
Thank you for trying to help.

17:29.362 --> 17:31.522
Whoever you are.

17:36.568 --> 17:38.258
Dan.

17:38.437 --> 17:42.167
I'm sorry I rearranged you.

17:44.075 --> 17:46.195
It's all right. big guy.

17:52.818 --> 17:55.878
Besides. what the hell can I do about it?

18:00.892 --> 18:05.302
So you're starting to edge your way
back into our lucid world. huh?

18:05.464 --> 18:06.764
I'm sorry. Harry.

18:06.931 --> 18:10.761
-Did getting drunk solve your problem?
-No.

18:11.334 --> 18:15.574
I still got the problem.
plus I got sick and ruined a cab.

18:16.706 --> 18:19.836
Listen. Bull. for what it's worth.
I think I know how you feel.

18:20.009 --> 18:22.309
I've been through stuff like this
in my life.

18:22.478 --> 18:25.538
It just seems so unfair. Harry.

18:30.552 --> 18:33.212
I mean. I thought I understood things.

18:33.388 --> 18:36.788
And then Selma died. and now....

18:37.225 --> 18:40.485
Now I don't know
what the hell's going on.

18:48.603 --> 18:51.333
What's life all about. Harry?

18:52.673 --> 18:54.703
I don't know. Bull.

18:56.343 --> 19:00.843
I don't know why we live.
and I don't know why we die.

19:03.149 --> 19:05.209
But I do know...

19:05.852 --> 19:08.012
...that as long as we're here...

19:08.187 --> 19:12.277
...we better hold on to each other
real tight.

19:29.909 --> 19:33.709
In case you're interested.
the music has stopped.

19:38.751 --> 19:41.481
-What can I do for you?
-I'm here for the job.

19:41.654 --> 19:43.624
What job is that?

19:43.789 --> 19:46.259
What is this. a wet suit?

19:47.159 --> 19:49.249
Well. we interviewed for bailiffs
last week.

19:49.428 --> 19:51.158
I'm late.

19:51.329 --> 19:53.589
Now. do I get the job or what?

19:54.999 --> 19:59.769
Well. there are certain procedural things
that we do. such as checking references.

20:00.405 --> 20:02.425
I don't have any.

20:02.906 --> 20:06.136
Well. that streamlines things.
How about experience?

20:06.310 --> 20:07.570
I'm a bailiff.

20:07.744 --> 20:11.314
-For how long?
-A hundred and six years.

20:15.686 --> 20:18.046
What's with the hair?

20:19.656 --> 20:22.676
I know he looks funny.
but don't say anything about it.

20:25.561 --> 20:29.551
You are a weird man.

20:32.867 --> 20:35.057
Can I keep her, Harry?

20:41.776 --> 20:45.906
-Why do I suddenly feel like a hamster?
-It's a long story.

20:46.081 --> 20:48.021
-I don't wanna hear it.
-You're hired.

20:49.283 --> 20:51.343
-Bull. you wanna show her around?
-Come on.

20:51.518 --> 20:54.818
I'll go show you where we stand
for eight hours a night.

20:54.989 --> 20:56.819
I quit.

20:57.524 --> 20:59.124
You can lean on me if you want.

20:59.292 --> 21:03.992
Well. how about
if I just hang a swing on your arm?

21:05.398 --> 21:07.028
A|rightY-

21:11.504 --> 21:14.104
I'll be needing a raise.

21:18.143 --> 21:19.173
Dirk. I got an idea.

21:19.344 --> 21:23.254
I'll go with you to the banquet.
and I'll explain it to your folks.

21:24.583 --> 21:26.453
No.

21:26.618 --> 21:28.608
They'd kill you.

21:32.591 --> 21:34.251
-Good night.
-Good night. Your Honor.

21:34.425 --> 21:36.415
It's after work. You can call me Harry.

21:37.261 --> 21:38.701
Someday.

21:38.863 --> 21:40.803
Christine.

21:41.298 --> 21:43.128
Wanna go grab a bite?

21:44.334 --> 21:46.034
I can't. I'm busy.

21:47.904 --> 21:51.434
I'm going to Dirk's party.
Bull said there'll be a ton of food there.

21:53.443 --> 21:56.543
Must've cost him a fortune.

22:11.661 --> 22:13.031
Are you all right?

22:13.529 --> 22:17.489
-Hangover.
-Serves you right.

22:18.600 --> 22:23.400
Anybody that abuses alcohol should be
punished with violent headaches...

22:23.572 --> 22:26.912
...the kind that makes your eyes fall out.

22:28.710 --> 22:30.470
Thank you.

22:31.578 --> 22:33.138
For what?

22:33.814 --> 22:36.584
Selma used to care enough
to yell at me too.

22:39.486 --> 22:41.676
Say. tell me something.

22:41.855 --> 22:44.375
What was this Selma like?

22:45.959 --> 22:50.159
Well. she was kind of abrasive.

22:52.099 --> 22:53.399
She was short.

22:55.468 --> 22:57.228
And she had a funny voice.

23:01.173 --> 23:03.273
How pathetic.

23:19.458 --> 23:20.928
BULL:
Quite a story, huh?

23:21.093 --> 23:25.223
SELMA:
I laughed, I cried. It became a part of me.

